(2121, 1, '2015-11-12 13:53:29', '2015-11-12 13:53:29', '<b>Chardonnay</b> (<small>pronounced: </small><span class="IPA" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)">[ʃaʁ.dɔ.nɛ]</span>) is a green-skinned grape variety used to make white <a title="Wine" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wine">w</a>i<a title="Wine" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wine">ne</a>. It originated in the <a title="Burgundy wine" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burgundy_wine">Burgundy wi</a>n<a title="Burgundy wine" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burgundy_wine">e</a>region of eastern France but is now grown wherever wine is produced, from England to New Zealand. For new and developing wine regions, growing Chardonnay is seen as a "rite of passage" and an easy entry into the international wine market.', 'Social Media Management', 'It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1298-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-11-12 13:53:29', '2015-11-12 13:53:29', '', 1298, 'http://tests.shahum.net/1298-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
