(2125, 1, '2015-11-12 14:03:27', '2015-11-12 14:03:27', '(Mos-cato) The moscato variety belongs to the muscat family of grapes - and so do moscatel and muscat ottonel.\r\n\r\n<b>Food pairings:</b> Moscato shows best on its own: without food but sweet wines will pair with dessert.\r\n\r\n<b>Districts:</b> moscato grows in most vine-friendly climates, including Italy, the Rhône Valley (where it is called muscat blanc à petits grains) and Austria (where it is called Muskateller).\r\n\r\n<b>Typical taste</b>: often sweet and always <b>fruity</b>, with a characteristic grapefruity and musky aroma. Moscato wines are easily recognizable to anyone who has tasted a Muscat table grape.', 'Moscato', '<b>Food pairings:</b> Moscato shows best on its own: without food but sweet wines will pair with dessert.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'moscato', '', '', '2015-11-12 14:03:27', '2015-11-12 14:03:27', '', 0, 'http://tests.shahum.net/?post_type=product&#038;p=2125', 0, 'product', '', 0),
